The Linux “du” (Disk Usage) is a standard Unix/Linux command.
Used to check the information of disk usage of files and directories.
The du command has many parameter options that can be used to get the results in many formats. 
The du command also displays the files and directory sizes in a recursively manner.

To get the summary of a grand total disk usage size of an directory use the option “-s” as follows.

The “-c” flag provides a grand total usage disk space at the last line.



